		"description": "<p>You enjoy cover fire provided by an ally in orbit, such as a satellite station directing hijacked asteroids or a shipâ€™s main gun. Your artillery has 4 shots, which recharge when you complete a long rest. As an action, you can launch up to all remaining shots, directing the target square for each within 120 feet.&nbsp;Each creature within 10 feet of a target square makes a Dexterity saving throw against your science save DC, taking 6d6 fire damage and 6d6 bludgeoning damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. A creature in more than one area of effect is only affected by one impact.</p>\n<p>At 16th level, the damage improves to 10d6 fire and 10d6 bludgeoning. Each shot produces a 20-foot radius sphere.</p>\n<p>At 18th level, the damage improves to 14d6 fire and 14d6 bludgeoning. Each shot produces a 40-foot radius sphere and your range increases to 1 mile (or in space combat, within the same star system).</p>",
